        <num>CCRP 881.5</num>
        <heading>881.5.  Correction of illegal sentence by trial court</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 881.5.  Correction of illegal sentence by trial court
On motion of the state or the defendant, or on its own motion, at any time, the court may correct a sentence imposed by that court which exceeds the maximum sentence authorized by law.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112861</p>
